  "text": "Among the artemisinins, artesunate is the most widely used perhaps, because of its solubility in water and availability for oral, intramuscular, intravenous and intra-rectal administration. Its conversion to dihy droartemisinin is fastest among this class of drugs and is said to occur with a t 1/2 of 2-3 min [CITATION_1] producing antimalarial effect approximately 4-5 times that of artemisinin [CITATION_2] . Its biological effect is therefore largely attributed to dihy droartemisinin generated in vivo (Woodrow et al., 2005) .",
